\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sl276\slmult1\cf1\f0\fs26 Aurumlux, a rich, expansive nation set directly to the east of the lowly, dilapidated Sapphire Coast, is a country in turmoil. Between the three classes of citizens, Royal, Labourist, and Barbaric, there is civil unrest. The upper-class, wealthy Royal families are in charge of most things. Shipping, trading, and mining. The Labourists are the common working class, who work the pubs, the shipping companies, and the general stores/markets. The Barbarians, however, are under the ball and chain of the "evil" Royal families, more particularly the Empyreal Kilbor family, who literally own the Barbarian population like slaves and uses them for cheap labor in the gem mines under the Three Peaks. The Barbarians were on the cusp of overthrowing the Empire when the late Emperor Kilbor the Third used his vast military forces to banish the Barbarians to the gem mines. All it would take is a few extra hands to help the Barbarians take back the castle, and claim Aurumlux for their rightful ownership, as it is their ancestral land.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Our hero, Ulvor, and his family of vagrants have made the journey from the desolate wastes of the Sapphire Coast, and have finally arrived in the bountiful land of Aurumlux in search of work. \par

