\pard\sl276\slmult1\qc\ul\b Detailed Characters List\ulnone\b0\par

\pard\sl276\slmult1\cf1 - Ulvor (Main Character): A young boy whose vagrant family is kidnapped upon arriving in Aurumlux. He gains the trust of the people of Aurumlux, and through honest jobs, gets the information he needs to bring down the Kilbor family for good.\par
\par
- Emperor Fennick Kilbor IV (Main Antagonist/Final Boss): A young Royal who is cast to the throne after the death of his father, Emperor Fennick Kilbor the Third. He is only a teenager, and is emotionally unstable, and doesn't fully understand the depth and complexities of politics. He was told by his late father to not let any new blood taint the soil of this once great land. The Barbarians are the ancestral race of Aurumlux, but they abandoned it eras ago once the Kilbor family claimed the throne and banished the impure Barbarians to the Sapphire Coast. Years later, when the Barbarians finally decided to wave the white flag and return to Aurumlux, the Emperor had Barbarians immediately banished to the gem mines, where they are never to leave. The Kilbor family has been in control of the country for so long, and they have been so blinded by wealth and power, that they no longer see that the races of Aurumlux are in turmoil. the new Emperor has carried his ancestral tradition wherein any new blood that enters the country is to be taken/arrested by Kilbor's secret guard, and are kept under lock and key in the dungeon below Kilbor Castle until a valuable purpose is discovered for them, usually cheap labor. If they prove to be of little to no use, they are dispatched. This murderous secret is the reason behind the kidnapping of Ulvor's family. \par
